Very solid recipe, and really easy. It was a big hit with Mr! I subbed panko for regular bread crumbs, and used thighs instead of drums. Didn't have mustard with horseradish on hand, but a mixture of dijon, whole grain mustard and a big glob of horseradish did the trick. I think next time I'll cook the coated chicken on a rack, though, so it's crispy on all surfaces.

