Rating: 3
I made this dish with organic, antibiotic-free chicken thighs(tastes so much better than other chicken and doesn't shrink as much when cooked). I also added radicchio for color and extra flavor. It was absolutely delicious..we scarfed it down! I always use organic apple cider vinegar because the commercial kind tastes like turpentine. Bragg Organic apple cider vinegar is found in health food stores and tastes sweet and light, not sharp and acidic like Heinz or America's Choice. Try it in salad dressings, you'll notice a difference! Will definitely make this recipe again..so easy!

Rating: 3
This was great! My boyfriend loved it so much, he leftovers the next day for lunch AND dinner. I think using good mustard is the key. I used Stonewall Kitchen's Mustard with Horseradish. Also, make sure you use cider vinegar for the dressing, regular vinegar doesn't have the right flavor. The citrus salad (recommended in the recipe) was a wonderful accompaniament.

